<task id="AIPU2-023" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build InternalIndexProvider — AI Search Citation Verification</title>
    <phase>2B</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai-safety, ai-search</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-022</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build InternalIndexProvider, an IVerificationProvider implementation that verifies citations against the
    spaarke-references Azure AI Search index — the internal knowledge base of authoritative legal references
    indexed from uploaded matter documents and curated legal sources. This provider handles CaseLaw, Statute,
    and Regulation types that have been ingested into the internal index, providing the highest-confidence
    verification path since it references Spaarke's own curated content.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET backend engineer with Azure AI Search SDK experience and Spaarke RAG patterns.</role>
  <goal>
    InternalIndexProvider queries the spaarke-references AI Search index, returns a CitationVerificationResult
    with IsVerified=true and a confidence score when the citation text matches an indexed document, and returns
    IsVerified=false with ConfidenceScore=0 when no match is found.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-rag-references.json</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IRagService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read IRagService.cs and spaarke-rag-references.json to understand the existing AI Search index structure, field names, scoring profiles, and how the search client is currently configured.</step>
    <step>Create InternalIndexProvider.cs in Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/ implementing IVerificationProvider.</step>
    <step>Set ProviderName = "InternalIndex" and SupportedTypes = [CitationType.CaseLaw, CitationType.Statute, CitationType.Regulation].</step>
    <step>Implement VerifyAsync(Citation citation, CancellationToken ct): build a SearchOptions with filter on citationType field (matching citation.CitationType.ToString()), search query = citation.NormalizedKey, top = 3, select fields [id, title, content, sourceUrl, citationKey]. Use the existing SearchClient for the spaarke-references index (inject via IConfiguration["AiSearch:ReferencesIndexName"]).</step>
    <step>Score the top result: if top result score &gt;= 0.85, return IsVerified=true, ConfidenceScore mapped from search score (normalize to 0-1), SourceUrl and VerifiedText from result. If score &lt; 0.85 or no results, return IsVerified=false, ConfidenceScore=0.</step>
    <step>Implement SearchAsync(string query, CancellationToken ct): free-text search on the references index, return up to 5 Citation objects constructed from results.</step>
    <step>Implement GetFullTextAsync(Citation citation, CancellationToken ct): look up by citationKey field exact match, return content field of the first result, or null if not found.</step>
    <step>Handle search failures: SearchRequestFailedException → log and return IsVerified=false (no exception propagated).</step>
    <step>Register InternalIndexProvider as IVerificationProvider in AddAiSafetyModule().</step>
    <step>Write unit tests with mocked SearchClient: high-score result → verified, low-score result → not verified, no results → not verified, SearchRequestFailedException → not verified.</step>
    <step>Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test --filter "InternalIndexProvider"` to verify.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>InternalIndexProvider is registered as IVerificationProvider for CaseLaw, Statute, and Regulation types.</criterion>
    <criterion>Search query uses citation.NormalizedKey against the spaarke-references index.</criterion>
    <criterion>Top result with score &gt;= 0.85 returns IsVerified=true with SourceUrl and VerifiedText populated.</criterion>
    <criterion>Score &lt; 0.85 or no results returns IsVerified=false, ConfidenceScore=0.</criterion>
    <criterion>SearchAsync returns up to 5 Citation objects from free-text search.</criterion>
    <criterion>GetFullTextAsync returns content of exact citationKey match, or null.</criterion>
    <criterion>Search exceptions are caught and return IsVerified=false (never propagated).</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass: `dotnet test --filter "InternalIndexProvider"`.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
